1778591201s:4692:"<h1 id="bkmrk-markdown-guide-%28with">Markdown Guide (with Examples)</h1>
<p id="bkmrk-markdown-is-a-simple">Markdown is a simple way to format text using plain characters. It’s widely used for notes, documentation, GitHub READMEs, blogs, and more.</p>
<hr id="bkmrk-">
<h2 id="bkmrk-1.-headings">1. Headings</h2>
<p id="bkmrk-use-%23-to-create-head">Use <code>#</code> to create headings.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-heading-1-%23%23-headi"><code class="language-md"># Heading 1
## Heading 2
### Heading 3
#### Heading 4
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-example-output%3A">Example output:</h3>
<h1 id="bkmrk-heading-1">Heading 1</h1>
<h2 id="bkmrk-heading-2">Heading 2</h2>
<h3 id="bkmrk-heading-3">Heading 3</h3>
<hr id="bkmrk--1">
<h2 id="bkmrk-2.-bold-and-italic-t">2. Bold and Italic Text</h2>
<h3 id="bkmrk-bold">Bold</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-use-%2A%2Adouble-asteris">Use <code>**double asterisks**</code> or <code>__double underscores__</code>.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-%2A%2Athis-is-bold-text%2A"><code class="language-md">**This is bold text**
__This is also bold__
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-italic">Italic</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-use-%2Asingle-asterisk">Use <code>*single asterisks*</code> or <code>_underscores_</code>.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-%2Athis-is-italic-text"><code class="language-md">*This is italic text*
_This is also italic_
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-bold-%2B-italic">Bold + Italic</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-%2A%2A%2Athis-is-bold-and-"><code class="language-md">***This is bold and italic***
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--2">
<h2 id="bkmrk-3.-lists">3. Lists</h2>
<h3 id="bkmrk-unordered-lists">Unordered Lists</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-use--%2C-%2A%2C-or-%2B.">Use <code>-</code>, <code>*</code>, or <code>+</code>.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk---apples---bananas--"><code class="language-md">- Apples
- Bananas
- Oranges
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-ordered-lists">Ordered Lists</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-use-numbers.">Use numbers.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-1.-first-item-2.-sec"><code class="language-md">1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--3">
<h2 id="bkmrk-4.-links">4. Links</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-%5Bopenai%5D%28https%3A%2F%2Fwww"><code class="language-md">[OpenAI](https://www.openai.com)
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--4">
<h2 id="bkmrk-5.-images">5. Images</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-%21%5Balt-text%5D%28https%3A%2F%2F"><code class="language-md">![Alt text](https://example.com/image.jpg)
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--5">
<h2 id="bkmrk-6.-code">6. Code</h2>
<h3 id="bkmrk-inline-code">Inline code</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-use-backticks-%60%3A">Use backticks <code>`</code>:</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-use-the-%60print%28%29%60-fu"><code class="language-md">Use the `print()` function in Python.
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-code-blocks">Code blocks</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-use-triple-backticks">Use triple backticks:</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-%60%60%60python-def-hello%28"><code class="language-md">```python
def hello():
    print("Hello, world!")
</code></pre>
<pre id="bkmrk-----%23%23-7.-blockquote"><code>
---

## 7. Blockquotes

Use `&gt;`:

```md
&gt; This is a quote.
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--6">
<h2 id="bkmrk-8.-horizontal-line">8. Horizontal Line</h2>
<p id="bkmrk-use-three-dashes%3A">Use three dashes:</p>
<pre id="bkmrk----"><code class="language-md">---
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--7">
<h2 id="bkmrk-9.-tables">9. Tables</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-%7C-name-%7C-age-%7C-city-"><code class="language-md">| Name   | Age | City    |
|--------|-----|---------|
| Alice  | 14  | London  |
| Bob    | 15  | Paris   |
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--8">
<h2 id="bkmrk-10.-checkboxes-%28task">10. Checkboxes (Task Lists)</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk---%5Bx%5D-learn-markdown"><code class="language-md">- [x] Learn Markdown
- [ ] Build a project
- [ ] Master formatting
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--9">
<h2 id="bkmrk-11.-escaping-charact">11. Escaping Characters</h2>
<p id="bkmrk-if-you-want-to-show-">If you want to show special characters, use a backslash <code>\</code>.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-%5C%2Athis-is-not-italic"><code class="language-md">\*This is not italic\*
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--10">
<h2 id="bkmrk-12.-combining-everyt">12. Combining Everything</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-my-notes-%23%23-today%E2%80%99"><code class="language-md"># My Notes

## Today’s Tasks

- [x] Study Markdown
- [ ] Practice coding

### Reminder

&gt; “Practice makes progress.”

Check [this site](https://maghrebvacc.com) for more info.

```
</code></pre>
